div1.p:
MICHAEL LYNCH
. I am a carman , and live in Water-lane, Fleet-street. The prisoner had access to my yard, (which is in Bouverie-street
) being employed to repair some houses in Shoe-lane. My chaise was in the yard - I saw it safe on Sunday, the 4th of January, and missed it on the Tuesday morning about nine o'clock, and on the Thursday following found part of it in possession of Norman, at Chelsea, and know it to be mine. I had given the prisoner leave to make his mortar up in my yard, but not at this time.
